# HTTP security headers for the static PWA shell (architecture §13, CP-7.1).
# Format read by Netlify and Cloudflare Pages ONLY.
#
# THE PRODUCTION DEPLOY IS VERCEL, WHICH IGNORES THIS FILE — the live header set is
# in `vercel.json` (which also carries the SPA "rewrites" this format cannot express).
# This file is kept so the header set stays portable to Netlify/Cloudflare: if you
# edit one, edit both, and verify with the curl in docs/HARDENING.md §1.
#
# `connect-src` allowlists exactly the production Supabase origin and its realtime
# socket. If the project ref changes, change it here AND in vercel.json.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://mlmqiopviyrobtemitaz.supabase.co wss://mlmqiopviyrobtemitaz.supabase.co; manifest-src 'self'; worker-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; object-src 'none'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

# Never let the service worker or the app entry go stale — always revalidate so a
# new deploy is picked up. Authenticated financial responses are served directly
# by Supabase (never by this host) and are marked no-store there / NetworkOnly in
# the service worker, so no Cache-Control is needed for them here.
/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache
/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache
